  16. (** Result values.

  18.     Result values handle computation results and errors in an explicit
  19.     and declarative manner without resorting to exceptions.

  21.     @since 4.08 *)

  23. (** {1:results Results} *)

  25. ‌type ('a, 'e) t = ('a, 'e) result = Ok of 'a | Error of 'e (**)
  26. (** The type for result values. Either a value [Ok v] or an error [Error e]. *)

  28. ‌val ok : 'a -> ('a, 'e) result
  29. (** [ok v] is [Ok v]. *)

  31. ‌val error : 'e -> ('a, 'e) result
  32. (** [error e] is [Error e]. *)

  34. val value : ('a, 'e) result -> default:'a -> 'a
  35. (** [value r ~default] is [v] if [r] is [Ok v] and [default] otherwise. *)

  37. ‌val get_ok : ('a, 'e) result -> 'a
  38. (** [get_ok r] is [v] if [r] is [Ok v] and raise otherwise.

  40.     @raise Invalid_argument if [r] is [Error _]. *)

  42. ‌val get_error : ('a, 'e) result -> 'e
  43. (** [get_error r] is [e] if [r] is [Error e] and raise otherwise.

  45.     @raise Invalid_argument if [r] is [Ok _]. *)

  47. ‌val bind : ('a, 'e) result -> ('a -> ('b, 'e) result) -> ('b, 'e) result
  48. (** [bind r f] is [f v] if [r] is [Ok v] and [r] if [r] is [Error _]. *)

  50. ‌val join : (('a, 'e) result, 'e) result -> ('a, 'e) result
  51. (** [join rr] is [r] if [rr] is [Ok r] and [rr] if [rr] is [Error _]. *)

  53. ‌val map : ('a -> 'b) -> ('a, 'e) result -> ('b, 'e) result
  54. (** [map f r] is [Ok (f v)] if [r] is [Ok v] and [r] if [r] is [Error _]. *)

  56. ‌val map_error : ('e -> 'f) -> ('a, 'e) result -> ('a, 'f) result
  57. (** [map_error f r] is [Error (f e)] if [r] is [Error e] and [r] if
  58.     [r] is [Ok _]. *)

  60. ‌val fold : ok:('a -> 'c) -> error:('e -> 'c) -> ('a, 'e) result -> 'c
  61. (** [fold ~ok ~error r] is [ok v] if [r] is [Ok v] and [error e] if [r]
  62.     is [Error e]. *)

  64. ‌val iter : ('a -> unit) -> ('a, 'e) result -> unit
  65. (** [iter f r] is [f v] if [r] is [Ok v] and [()] otherwise. *)

  67. ‌val iter_error : ('e -> unit) -> ('a, 'e) result -> unit
  68. (** [iter_error f r] is [f e] if [r] is [Error e] and [()] otherwise. *)

  70. (** {1:preds Predicates and comparisons} *)

  72. ‌val is_ok : ('a, 'e) result -> bool
  73. (** [is_ok r] is [true] if and only if [r] is [Ok _]. *)

  75. ‌val is_error : ('a, 'e) result -> bool
  76. (** [is_error r] is [true] if and only if [r] is [Error _]. *)

  78. ‌val equal :
  79.   ok:('a -> 'a -> bool) -> error:('e -> 'e -> bool) -> ('a, 'e) result ->
  80.   ('a, 'e) result -> bool
  81. (** [equal ~ok ~error r0 r1] tests equality of [r0] and [r1] using [ok]
  82.     and [error] to respectively compare values wrapped by [Ok _] and
  83.     [Error _]. *)

  85. ‌val compare :
  86.   ok:('a -> 'a -> int) -> error:('e -> 'e -> int) -> ('a, 'e) result ->
  87.   ('a, 'e) result -> int
  88. (** [compare ~ok ~error r0 r1] totally orders [r0] and [r1] using [ok] and
  89.     [error] to respectively compare values wrapped by [Ok _ ] and [Error _].
  90.     [Ok _] values are smaller than [Error _] values. *)

  92. (** {1:convert Converting} *)

  94. ‌val to_option : ('a, 'e) result -> 'a option
  95. (** [to_option r] is [r] as an option, mapping [Ok v] to [Some v] and
  96.     [Error _] to [None]. *)

  98. ‌val to_list : ('a, 'e) result -> 'a list
  99. (** [to_list r] is [[v]] if [r] is [Ok v] and [[]] otherwise. *)

  101. ‌val to_seq : ('a, 'e) result -> 'a Seq.t
  102. (** [to_seq r] is [r] as a sequence. [Ok v] is the singleton sequence
  103.     containing [v] and [Error _] is the empty sequence. *)
